 <fr:p>The corrected counit <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\epsilon ' \colon  g\circ  f\sim  1_{A}]]></fr:tex> is defined like so:</fr:p>
 <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[   \epsilon ' x :\equiv    \epsilon \mathopen {}\left ({f\mathopen {}\left ({f^{-1} x}\right )\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}^{-1} \cdot  \mathsf {act}_{f}\mathopen {}\left ({\eta \mathopen {}\left ({f^{-1} x}\right )\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {} \cdot  \epsilon  x  ]]></fr:tex>

 <fr:p>The coherence <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\chi \colon  \mathsf {act}_{f}\circ  \eta  \sim  \epsilon '\circ  f]]></fr:tex> can be constructed using our two naturality lemmas <fr:ref
addr="erct-001V"
taxon="Lemma" /> and <fr:ref
addr="erct-001W"
taxon="Lemma" />.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree>
 
