xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>2253</fr:anchor><fr:addr>#293</fr:addr><fr:route>unstable-293.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>2</fr:month><fr:day>18</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
type="local"
href="jonmsterling.xml"
addr="jonmsterling"
title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:parent>erct-0049</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <fr:p>Fixing <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x,y:A]]></fr:tex> we must show that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {act}_{f}\colon  x = y \to  fx=fy]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-000W.xml"
addr="erct-000W"
title="Inverse">invertible</fr:link>. By <fr:ref
addr="erct-002C"
taxon="Lemma" /> and <fr:ref
addr="erct-002D"
taxon="Lemma" />, it suffices to exhibit a <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-000U.xml"
addr="erct-000U"
title="Biinverse">biinverse</fr:link> to <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {act}_{f}]]></fr:tex> (it is convenient that the underlying maps of the <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-000Y.xml"
addr="erct-000Y"
title="Section-retraction pair">section</fr:link> and <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-000Y.xml"
addr="erct-000Y"
title="Section-retraction pair">retraction</fr:link> need not be identical).</fr:p>

 <fr:p>We first define the <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-000Y.xml"
addr="erct-000Y"
title="Section-retraction pair">sections</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[s_{x,y}\colon  fx = fy \to  x = y]]></fr:tex>. Because <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> is assumed to be <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-001T.xml"
addr="erct-001T"
title="N-truncated map">propositional</fr:link>, we have by <fr:ref
addr="erct-001R"
taxon="Example" /> an assignment <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\phi _{x,y}: \mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{\mathopen {}\left ({h:fx=fy}\right )\mathclose {}}}{\textstyle \prod _{\mathopen {}\left ({h:fx=fy}\right )\mathclose {}}}{\scriptstyle \prod _{\mathopen {}\left ({h:fx=fy}\right )\mathclose {}}}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{\mathopen {}\left ({h:fx=fy}\right )\mathclose {}}} \mathopen {}\left ({x,\mathsf {refl}}\right )\mathclose {}\cong _{\mathsf {fiber}\,f\,\mathopen {}\left ({fx}\right )\mathclose {}}\mathopen {}\left ({y,h^{-1}}\right )\mathclose {}]]></fr:tex>. We therefore define <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[s_{x,y}h :\equiv  \mathopen {}\left ({\phi _{x,y}h}\right )\mathclose {}.1]]></fr:tex>; the witness of <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-000Y.xml"
addr="erct-000Y"
title="Section-retraction pair">sectionhood</fr:link> can be constructed using <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathopen {}\left ({\phi _{x,y}h}\right )\mathclose {}.2]]></fr:tex> modulo some identification algebra.</fr:p>

 <fr:p>To construct the <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-000Y.xml"
addr="erct-000Y"
title="Section-retraction pair">retractions</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[r_{x,y}\colon  fx=fy\to  x = y]]></fr:tex>, we note by our assumption that we have an assignment <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\psi _{x,y}:\mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{\mathopen {}\left ({h:fx=fy}\right )\mathclose {}}}{\textstyle \prod _{\mathopen {}\left ({h:fx=fy}\right )\mathclose {}}}{\scriptstyle \prod _{\mathopen {}\left ({h:fx=fy}\right )\mathclose {}}}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{\mathopen {}\left ({h:fx=fy}\right )\mathclose {}}} \mathopen {}\left ({x,\mathsf {refl}}\right )\mathclose {} =_{\mathsf {fiber}\,f\,\mathopen {}\left ({fx}\right )\mathclose {}} \mathopen {}\left ({y,h^{-1}}\right )\mathclose {}]]></fr:tex>, and we define <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[r_{x,y}h :\equiv  \mathsf {act}_{-.1}\mathopen {}\left ({\psi _{x,y}h}\right )\mathclose {}]]></fr:tex>. It remains to show that for all <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x,y:A]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[h\colon  x =y]]></fr:tex>, we have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {act}_{-.1}\mathopen {}\left ({\psi _{x,y}h}\right )\mathclose {}=h]]></fr:tex>. By induction on <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[h]]></fr:tex> it suffices to show that for all <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x:A]]></fr:tex> we have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {act}_{-.1}\mathopen {}\left ({\psi _{x,x}\mathsf {refl}}\right )\mathclose {} = \mathsf {refl}]]></fr:tex>. We will deduce that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\psi _{x,x}\mathsf {refl} = \mathsf {refl}]]></fr:tex> from our assumption that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\to  B]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-001T.xml"
addr="erct-001T"
title="N-truncated map">propositional</fr:link> and thus <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-001T.xml"
addr="erct-001T"
title="N-truncated map">fibred in sets</fr:link> via <fr:ref
addr="erct-001L"
taxon="Lemma" />.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree>
 
